with short-term assets. The current ratio in all periods was adversely affected by the fact that Chevron’s inventories are valued on a
last-in, first-out basis. At year-end 2021, the book value of inventory was lower than replacement costs, based on average
acquisition costs during the year, by approximately $5.6 billion.
